<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8"/>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
<title>CDIS 300 — Fiametta Boffey</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400;1,600&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet"/>
<style>
*{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
:root{
  --bg:#faf8f4;--ink:#1c1a17;--muted:#8a8478;--rule:#ddd9d0;
  --audi:#1a6b8a;--neuro-r:#7b3f8c;--neuro-f:#3d5a8e;
  --resp:#2e7d5e;--phon:#8b2635;--reso:#b5621a;--arti:#4a6741;
  --surface:#fff;--surface2:#f4f1eb;
}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
body{font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;background:var(--bg);color:var(--ink);overflow-x:hidden}

/* ── STICKY NAV ── */
#topnav{
  position:fixed;top:0;left:0;right:0;z-index:200;
  background:rgba(250,248,244,0.92);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);
  border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);
  padding:.7rem 2rem;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;
}
#topnav .nav-brand{
  font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.6rem;letter-spacing:.12em;
  text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-right:.8rem;white-space:nowrap;
}
.nav-btn{
  padding:.3rem .85rem;border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:99px;
  background:none;cursor:pointer;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-size:.72rem;
  color:var(--muted);transition:all .2s;text-decoration:none;white-space:nowrap;
}
.nav-btn:hover{color:var(--ink);border-color:var(--ink)}
.nav-btn.active{color:var(--surface);border-color:var(--ink);background:var(--ink)}
.nav-btn.b-audi{--nc:var(--audi)}
.nav-btn.b-neuro-r{--nc:var(--neuro-r)}
.nav-btn.b-neuro-f{--nc:var(--neuro-f)}
.nav-btn.b-resp{--nc:var(--resp)}
.nav-btn.b-phon{--nc:var(--phon)}
.nav-btn.b-reso{--nc:var(--reso)}
.nav-btn.b-arti{--nc:var(--arti)}
.nav-btn:hover{color:var(--nc,var(--ink));border-color:var(--nc,var(--ink));background:transparent}

/* ── HERO ── */
#hero{
  min-height:100vh;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  padding:7rem 5vw 4rem;gap:3rem;align-items:center;
  border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);
}
.hero-left{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.5rem}
.hero-tag{
  font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.65rem;
  letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);
}
.hero-title{
  font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:clamp(2.6rem,5vw,4.2rem);
  font-weight:700;line-height:1.08;
}
.hero-title em{font-style:italic;color:var(--audi)}
.hero-premise{
  font-size:.95rem;line-height:1.75;color:#555;max-width:480px;
  border-left:3px solid var(--rule);padding-left:1rem;
}
.hero-premise strong{color:var(--ink)}
.hero-chips{display:flex;gap:.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:.5rem}
.hero-chip{
  padding:.35rem .9rem;border:1px solid;border-radius:99px;
  font-size:.68rem;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;letter-spacing:.05em;
  cursor:pointer;transition:all .22s;text-decoration:none;
  display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.4rem;
}
.hero-chip:hover{transform:translateY(-2px);box-shadow:0 5px 16px rgba(0,0,0,.1)}
.hc-audi{color:var(--audi);border-color:var(--audi);background:rgba(26,107,138,.06)}
.hc-neuro-r{color:var(--neuro-r);border-color:var(--neuro-r);background:rgba(123,63,140,.06)}
.hc-neuro-f{color:var(--neuro-f);border-color:var(--neuro-f);background:rgba(61,90,142,.06)}
.hc-resp{color:var(--resp);border-color:var(--resp);background:rgba(46,125,94,.06)}
.hc-phon{color:var(--phon);border-color:var(--phon);background:rgba(139,38,53,.06)}
.hc-reso{color:var(--reso);border-color:var(--reso);background:rgba(181,98,26,.06)}
.hc-arti{color:var(--arti);border-color:var(--arti);background:rgba(74,103,65,.06)}
.scroll-hint{
  font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.65rem;letter-spacing:.12em;
  color:var(--muted);display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;margin-top:1rem;
  animation:bob 2.2s ease-in-out infinite;
}
@keyframes bob{0%,100%{transform:translateY(0)}50%{transform:translateY(5px)}}
.hero-right{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center}
.hero-photo-frame{
  width:min(380px,100%);aspect-ratio:3/4;border-radius:8px;
  overflow:hidden;border:1px solid var(--rule);position:relative;
  background:var(--surface2);
}
.hero-photo-frame img{width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block}
.hero-photo-placeholder{
  width:100%;height:100%;display:flex;flex-direction:column;
  align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:.8rem;
  color:var(--muted);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;
  font-size:.68rem;letter-spacing:.08em;text-align:center;padding:2rem;
}
.photo-ph-icon{font-size:3rem;opacity:.3}
.hero-name-tag{
  position:absolute;bottom:0;left:0;right:0;
  background:linear-gradient(transparent,rgba(0,0,0,.55));
  padding:2rem 1.2rem .9rem;color:#fff;
}
.hero-name-tag h2{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:600}
.hero-name-tag p{font-size:.72rem;opacity:.8;margin-top:.2rem;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif}

/* ── SECTION WRAPPER ── */
.system-section{
  padding:5rem 5vw;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);
  scroll-margin-top:60px;
}
.sys-header{margin-bottom:2.5rem}
.sys-step-tag{
  font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.62rem;letter-spacing:.2em;
  text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:.5rem;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.6rem;
}
.sys-step-tag::before{content:'';display:inline-block;width:28px;height:2px;border-radius:1px}
.sys-title{
  font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,3.5vw,2.8rem);
  font-weight:700;line-height:1.15;margin-bottom:.6rem;
}
.sys-subtitle{font-size:.9rem;color:var(--muted);max-width:560px;line-height:1.6}

/* Section accent colors */
.sec-audi .sys-step-tag{color:var(--audi)} .sec-audi .sys-step-tag::before{background:var(--audi)}
.sec-neuro-r .sys-step-tag{color:var(--neuro-r)} .sec-neuro-r .sys-step-tag::before{background:var(--neuro-r)}
.sec-neuro-f .sys-step-tag{color:var(--neuro-f)} .sec-neuro-f .sys-step-tag::before{background:var(--neuro-f)}
.sec-resp .sys-step-tag{color:var(--resp)} .sec-resp .sys-step-tag::before{background:var(--resp)}
.sec-phon .sys-step-tag{color:var(--phon)} .sec-phon .sys-step-tag::before{background:var(--phon)}
.sec-reso .sys-step-tag{color:var(--reso)} .sec-reso .sys-step-tag::before{background:var(--reso)}
.sec-arti .sys-step-tag{color:var(--arti)} .sec-arti .sys-step-tag::before{background:var(--arti)}

/* ── TWO COL LAYOUT ── */
.two-col{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:2.5rem;align-items:start}
.two-col.flip{direction:rtl}.two-col.flip>*{direction:ltr}

/* ── HOTSPOT DIAGRAM ── */
.diagram-wrap{position:relative;border-radius:12px;overflow:visible;background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--rule)}
.diagram-img-area{position:relative;width:100%;aspect-ratio:4/3;overflow:hidden;border-radius:12px 12px 0 0}
.diagram-img-area img{width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block}
.diagram-placeholder{
  width:100%;height:100%;background:var(--surface2);
  display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;
  gap:.6rem;color:var(--muted);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;
  font-size:.65rem;letter-spacing:.06em;text-align:center;padding:1rem;
}
.diagram-caption{padding:.7rem 1rem;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.6rem;color:var(--muted);letter-spacing:.06em;border-top:1px solid var(--rule)}
.diagram-hint{
  display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;padding:.5rem 1rem .8rem;
  font-size:.72rem;color:var(--muted);
}
.pulse-dot-hint{width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--accent,#888);animation:pulse 1.8s infinite;flex-shrink:0}
@keyframes pulse{0%,100%{opacity:1;transform:scale(1)}50%{opacity:.5;transform:scale(1.3)}}

/* HOTSPOT */
.hotspot{
  position:absolute;width:22px;height:22px;border-radius:50%;
  border:2.5px solid #fff;cursor:pointer;transform:translate(-50%,-50%);
  display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;
  font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.55rem;font-weight:700;color:#fff;
  transition:transform .2s;z-index:10;
  box-shadow:0 0 0 4px rgba(255,255,255,.2),0 0 12px 2px currentColor;
}
.hotspot::after{
  content:'';position:absolute;inset:-4px;border-radius:50%;
  border:2px solid currentColor;animation:ring 2s infinite;opacity:.6;
}
@keyframes ring{0%{transform:scale(1);opacity:.6}100%{transform:scale(1.7);opacity:0}}
.hotspot:hover{transform:translate(-50%,-50%) scale(1.25)}
.hotspot.active{box-shadow:0 0 0 5px rgba(255,255,255,.4),0 0 20px 4px currentColor;transform:translate(-50%,-50%) scale(1.2)}

/* POPUP */
.hs-popup{
  position:absolute;z-index:50;width:280px;
  background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--rule);
  border-radius:12px;box-shadow:0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,.12);
  padding:1.1rem 1.2rem;
  opacity:0;pointer-events:none;transition:opacity .2s,transform .2s;
  transform:translateY(6px);
}
.hs-popup.visible{opacity:1;pointer-events:all;transform:translateY(0)}
.hs-popup .pop-label{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.6rem;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:.3rem}
.hs-popup h4{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:.5rem}
.hs-popup p{font-size:.78rem;line-height:1.65;color:#555}
.hs-popup .pop-close{
  position:absolute;top:.6rem;right:.7rem;background:none;border:none;
  cursor:pointer;font-size:1rem;color:var(--muted);line-height:1;
}
.hs-popup .pop-close:hover{color:var(--ink)}
.pop-accent{display:inline-block;width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;margin-right:.4rem;vertical-align:middle}

/* ── INFO PANEL (right side) ── */
.info-panel{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.2rem}
.info-intro{font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.75;color:#555;padding-bottom:1.2rem;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)}
.info-intro strong{color:var(--ink)}

/* ACCORDION */
.accordion-item{border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden}
.accordion-btn{
  width:100%;padding:.85rem 1.1rem;background:none;border:none;
  display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;
  cursor:pointer;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-size:.85rem;
  font-weight:500;color:var(--ink);text-align:left;transition:background .2s;
}
.accordion-btn:hover{background:var(--surface2)}
.accordion-btn .acc-icon{font-size:.7rem;color:var(--muted);transition:transform .25s;flex-shrink:0}
.accordion-btn.open .acc-icon{transform:rotate(180deg)}
.accordion-body{
  max-height:0;overflow:hidden;transition:max-height .35s ease;
  font-size:.8rem;line-height:1.7;color:#555;
}
.accordion-body-inner{padding:.1rem 1.1rem 1rem}
.accordion-body ul{padding-left:1rem;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.3rem}
.accordion-body ul li{list-style:none;padding-left:.8rem;position:relative}
.accordion-body ul li::before{content:'→';position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--muted);font-size:.65rem;top:.15rem}
.accordion-body ul li strong{color:var(--ink)}
.acc-label{
  font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.58rem;letter-spacing:.08em;
  text-transform:uppercase;padding:.15rem .5rem;border-radius:99px;margin-right:.5rem;
}

/* ── NEXT SECTION LINK ── */
.next-link{
  display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.7rem;padding:1rem 1.2rem;
  background:var(--surface2);border-radius:10px;border:1px solid var(--rule);
  text-decoration:none;color:var(--ink);font-size:.85rem;font-weight:500;
  transition:all .2s;margin-top:1rem;
}
.next-link:hover{border-color:var(--ink);transform:translateX(4px)}
.next-link .nl-arrow{font-size:1rem;transition:transform .2s}
.next-link:hover .nl-arrow{transform:translateX(4px)}
.next-link .nl-label{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.6rem;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);display:block}

/* ── PATHWAY STRIP ── */
.pathway-strip{
  display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0;flex-wrap:wrap;
  background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;
  margin:2rem 0;
}
.pw-node{
  flex:1;min-width:120px;padding:1rem .8rem;text-align:center;cursor:pointer;
  border-right:1px solid var(--rule);transition:background .2s;position:relative;
}
.pw-node:last-child{border-right:none}
.pw-node:hover,.pw-node.active{background:var(--surface2)}
.pw-node .pwn-step{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.55rem;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:.3rem}
.pw-node .pwn-name{font-size:.8rem;font-weight:500}
.pw-node .pwn-bar{height:3px;border-radius:2px;margin-top:.5rem;opacity:.3;transition:opacity .2s}
.pw-node.active .pwn-bar{opacity:1}
.pw-detail{background:var(--surface2);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:12px;padding:1.5rem;margin-bottom:2rem;min-height:100px;transition:all .2s}
.pw-detail h4{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:1.2rem;margin-bottom:.5rem}
.pw-detail p{font-size:.82rem;color:#555;line-height:1.65}

/* ── REFERENCES ── */
#references{padding:5rem 5vw 6rem;background:var(--surface2)}
#references h2{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:.5rem}
#references .ref-note{font-size:.8rem;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:2rem;font-style:italic}
.ref-list{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.75rem}
.ref-item{background:var(--surface);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:8px;padding:.9rem 1.2rem;font-size:.82rem;line-height:1.7;color:#555}
.ref-item strong{color:var(--ink)}

/* ── MODAL OVERLAY ── */
#modal-overlay{position:fixed;inset:0;background:rgba(0,0,0,.45);z-index:500;display:none;align-items:center;justify-content:center;padding:1rem}
#modal-overlay.open{display:flex}
.modal-box{background:var(--surface);border-radius:16px;max-width:480px;width:100%;padding:2rem;position:relative;max-height:90vh;overflow-y:auto;box-shadow:0 24px 64px rgba(0,0,0,.2)}
.modal-close{position:absolute;top:1rem;right:1rem;background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;font-size:1.3rem;color:var(--muted)}
.modal-close:hover{color:var(--ink)}
.modal-tag{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:.62rem;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:.4rem}
.modal-title{font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.2}
.modal-body{font-size:.85rem;line-height:1.75;color:#555}
.modal-body strong{color:var(--ink)}
.modal-body ul{padding-left:1.2rem;margin:.5rem 0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.3rem}
.modal-body ul li{list-style:none;padding-left:.7rem;position:relative;font-size:.82rem}
.modal-body ul li::before{content:'→';position:absolute;left:0;color:var(--muted);font-size:.65rem;top:.15rem}

/* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
@media(max-width:900px){
  #hero{grid-template-columns:1fr;padding:6rem 5vw 3rem}
  .hero-right{order:-1}
  .hero-photo-frame{aspect-ratio:1/1;max-width:280px;margin:0 auto}
  .two-col,.two-col.flip{grid-template-columns:1fr;direction:ltr}
  .pathway-strip{flex-direction:column}
  .pw-node{width:100%;border-right:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)}
  .pw-node:last-child{border-bottom:none}
}
@media(max-width:600px){
  .system-section{padding:4rem 5vw}
  #topnav{padding:.5rem 1rem;gap:.35rem}
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- ── TOP NAV ── -->
<nav id="topnav">
  <span class="nav-brand">CDIS 300</span>
  <a class="nav-btn b-audi" href="#auditory">👂 Auditory</a>
  <a class="nav-btn b-neuro-r" href="#neuro-receive">🧠 Neuro: Receive</a>
  <a class="nav-btn b-neuro-f" href="#neuro-formulate">🧠 Neuro: Respond</a>
  <a class="nav-btn b-resp" href="#respiratory">💨 Respiratory</a>
  <a class="nav-btn b-phon" href="#phonatory">〰 Phonatory</a>
  <a class="nav-btn b-reso" href="#resonatory">🔊 Resonatory</a>
  <a class="nav-btn b-arti" href="#articulatory">👄 Articulatory</a>
</nav>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════
     HERO
══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="hero">
  <div class="hero-left">
    <div class="hero-tag">CDIS 300 · A&amp;P of Speech-Language &amp; Hearing · Final Project</div>
    <h1 class="hero-title">
      "Do you<br/>like <em>cheese?</em>"
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-premise">
      Four words. Seven physiological systems. Milliseconds. This project traces the complete journey of human communication — from the moment <strong>sound enters the ear</strong> to the moment <strong>a spoken response leaves the lips</strong> — through every anatomical system that makes it possible.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-chips">
      <a class="hero-chip hc-audi" href="#auditory"><span>01</span> Auditory</a>
      <a class="hero-chip hc-neuro-r" href="#neuro-receive"><span>02</span> Neuro: Receive</a>
      <a class="hero-chip hc-neuro-f" href="#neuro-formulate"><span>03</span> Neuro: Respond</a>
      <a class="hero-chip hc-resp" href="#respiratory"><span>04</span> Respiratory</a>
      <a class="hero-chip hc-phon" href="#phonatory"><span>05</span> Phonatory</a>
      <a class="hero-chip hc-reso" href="#resonatory"><span>06</span> Resonatory</a>
      <a class="hero-chip hc-arti" href="#articulatory"><span>07</span> Articulatory</a>
    </div>
    <div class="scroll-hint">scroll to explore ↓</div>
  </div>
  <div class="hero-right">
    <div class="hero-photo-frame">
      <img src="FiaFace.png" alt="Fiametta Boffey"/>
      <div class="hero-name-tag">
        <h2>Fiametta Boffey</h2>
        <p>CDIS 300 · Mrs. Kinamon</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════
     01 — AUDITORY
══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="auditory" class="system-section sec-audi">
  <div class="sys-header">
    <div class="sys-step-tag">Step 01 · The Question Arrives</div>
    <h2 class="sys-title">Auditory System</h2>
    <p class="sys-subtitle">Before any response can be formed, the ear must capture, transduce, and transmit the acoustic signal of "Do you like cheese?" to the brain. Click the glowing circles on the diagram to explore each structure.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="two-col">
    <!-- DIAGRAM -->
    <div>
      <div class="diagram-wrap" id="diag-audi">
        <div class="diagram-img-area" id="diag-audi-img">
          <img src="Pinna.png" alt="Ear anatomy diagram"/>
          <!-- HOTSPOTS — positions are % from top-left; adjust after adding your image -->
          <div class="hotspot" style="left:18%;top:35%;color:var(--audi);background:var(--audi)" data-popup="hs-audi-1" title="Auricle/Pinna">1</div>
          <div class="hotspot" style="left:32%;top:50%;color:var(--audi);background:var(--audi)" data-popup="hs-audi-2" title="Tympanic Membrane">2</div>
          <div class="hotspot" style="left:50%;top:42%;color:var(--audi);background:var(--audi)" data-popup="hs-audi-3" title="Ossicles">3</div>
          <div class="hotspot" style="left:68%;top:38%;color:var(--audi);background:var(--audi)" data-popup="hs-audi-4" title="Cochlea">4</div>
          <div class="hotspot" style="left:82%;top:55%;color:var(--audi);background:var(--audi)" data-popup="hs-audi-5" title="CN VIII">5</div>
        </div>
        <!-- POPUPS -->
        <div class="hs-popup" id="hs-audi-1">
          <button class="pop-close" onclick="closePopup('hs-audi-1')">✕</button>
          <div class="pop-label"><span class="pop-accent" style="background:var(--audi)"></span>Outer Ear</div>
          <img src="Pinna.png" alt="Auricle / Pinna" style="width:100%;border-radius:6px;margin:.4rem 0 .5rem;aspect-ratio:4/3;object-fit:cover;display:block"/>
          <h4>Auricle / Pinna</h4>
          <p>Elastic cartilage covered by skin. Collects incoming sound waves and provides spectral cues for sound localization — especially elevation. The complex folds (helix, antihelix, tragus, concha) create direction-dependent filtering that the brain uses to judge where a sound is coming from.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hs-popup" id="hs-audi-2">
          <button class="pop-close" onclick="closePopup('hs-audi-2')">✕</button>
          <div class="pop-label"><span class="pop-accent" style="background:var(--audi)"></span>Outer / Middle Ear Border</div>
          <img src="AuditoryCanal.png" alt="Auditory canal" style="width:100%;border-radius:6px;margin:.4rem 0 .5rem;aspect-ratio:4/3;object-fit:cover;display:block"/>
          <h4>Tympanic Membrane</h4>
          <p>A thin cone-shaped membrane (~9–10 mm diameter) that separates the outer and middle ear. When "Do you like cheese?" arrives, the sound pressure waves cause the eardrum to vibrate. It is attached to the malleus at the umbo, transferring vibrations directly into the ossicular chain.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hs-popup" id="hs-audi-3">
          <button class="pop-close" onclick="closePopup('hs-audi-3')">✕</button>
          <div class="pop-label"><span class="pop-accent" style="background:var(--audi)"></span>Middle Ear</div>
          <img src="ossicularchain.png" alt="Ossicular chain" style="width:100%;border-radius:6px;margin:.4rem 0 .5rem;aspect-ratio:4/3;object-fit:cover;display:block"/>
          <h4>Ossicles: Malleus, Incus &amp; Stapes</h4>
          <p>The three smallest bones in the human body. The <strong>malleus</strong> receives vibration from the eardrum, passes it to the <strong>incus</strong>, and then to the <strong>stapes</strong> whose footplate sits in the oval window. Together they provide ~25–30 dB of impedance matching gain — overcoming the acoustic mismatch between air and cochlear fluid. The <strong>stapedius muscle (CN VII)</strong> stiffens the chain to protect against loud sounds (acoustic reflex).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hs-popup" id="hs-audi-4">
          <button class="pop-close" onclick="closePopup('hs-audi-4')">✕</button>
          <div class="pop-label"><span class="pop-accent" style="background:var(--audi)"></span>Inner Ear</div>
          <img src="osseouslabyrinth.png" alt="Osseous labyrinth / Cochlea" style="width:100%;border-radius:6px;margin:.4rem 0 .5rem;aspect-ratio:4/3;object-fit:cover;display:block"/>
          <h4>Cochlea</h4>
          <p>A fluid-filled, snail-shaped structure (~2.5 turns) where mechanical vibration becomes neural signal. The <strong>basilar membrane</strong> responds to different frequencies at different places — high frequencies at the base, low frequencies at the apex (Place Theory, von Békésy, 1960). The <strong>Organ of Corti</strong> sits on the basilar membrane and contains ~3,500 inner hair cells (primary sensors) and ~12,000 outer hair cells (cochlear amplifier, +40–60 dB gain).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hs-popup" id="hs-audi-5">
          <button class="pop-close" onclick="closePopup('hs-audi-5')">✕</button>
          <div class="pop-label"><span class="pop-accent" style="background:var(--audi)"></span>Neural Output</div>
          <h4>CN VIII — Vestibulocochlear Nerve</h4>
          <p>The cochlear branch of CN VIII carries tonotopically organized neural signals from the spiral ganglion neurons to the cochlear nuclei in the brainstem. From here the signal ascends: cochlear nuclei → superior olivary complex → inferior colliculus → medial geniculate body (thalamus) → primary auditory cortex (Heschl's gyrus, BA 41/42) → Wernicke's area for comprehension.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram-caption">Fig. 1 — Ear anatomy. Click the numbered hotspots to explore each structure.</div>
        <div class="diagram-hint"><div class="pulse-dot-hint" style="--accent:var(--audi)"></div> Click the glowing circles to learn about each structure</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- INFO PANEL -->
    <div class="info-panel">
      <div class="info-intro">
        The ear is divided into three sections: the <strong>outer ear</strong> (collection), the <strong>middle ear</strong> (impedance matching), and the <strong>inner ear</strong> (transduction). The entire journey from sound wave to neural signal takes only a few milliseconds.
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-btn" onclick="toggleAcc(this)">
          <span><span class="acc-label" style="background:rgba(26,107,138,.1);color:var(--audi)">Outer Ear</span>Collection &amp; Funneling</span>
          <span class="acc-icon">▼</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body"><div class="accordion-body-inner"><ul>
          <li>Auricle/Pinna collects sound and provides directional cues</li>
          <li><strong>External auditory meatus (EAM):</strong> ~2.5 cm canal; resonates at 3–4 kHz, boosting high-frequency consonants by ~10–15 dB — critical for speech intelligibility</li>
          <li><strong>Tympanic membrane:</strong> Vibrates in response to sound pressure; transfers motion to malleus</li>
        </ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-btn" onclick="toggleAcc(this)">
          <span><span class="acc-label" style="background:rgba(26,107,138,.1);color:var(--audi)">Middle Ear</span>Impedance Matching</span>
          <span class="acc-icon">▼</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body"><div class="accordion-body-inner"><ul>
          <li><strong>Without ossicles:</strong> ~99.9% of sound energy would be reflected at the oval window</li>
          <li><strong>Area ratio (TM : stapes footplate):</strong> ~55 mm² : 3.2 mm² = ~17:1 pressure gain</li>
          <li><strong>Ossicular lever ratio:</strong> adds additional ~1.3:1 force multiplication</li>
          <li><strong>Total gain:</strong> ~25–30 dB — recovers the air-to-fluid mismatch loss</li>
          <li><strong>Eustachian tube:</strong> Equalizes pressure; opens during swallowing/yawning</li>
        </ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="accordion-item">
        <button class="accordion-btn" onclick="toggleAcc(this)">
          <span><span class="acc-label" style="background:rgba(26,107,138,.1);color:var(--audi)">Inner Ear</span>Transduction</span>
          <span class="acc-icon">▼</span>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-body"><div class="accordion-body-inner"><ul>
          <li><strong>Scala vestibuli:</strong> Perilymph; receives oval window vibrations</li>
          <li><strong>Scala media:</strong> Endolymph; houses the Organ of Corti</li>
          <li><strong>Scala tympani:</strong> Perilymph; terminates at round window</li>
          <li><strong>Basilar membrane tonotopy:</strong> Base = high freq; Apex = low freq (Place Theory)</li>
          <li><strong>Outer hair cells:</strong> Active amplification; damage → sensorineural hearing loss</li>
        </ul></div></div>
      </div>
      <a class="next-link hc-neuro-r" href="#neuro-receive">
        <div><span class="nl-label">Next →</span>Neurological System: Receiving &amp; Understanding</div>
        <span class="nl-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

