          <div class="pop-label"><span class="pop-accent" style="background:var(--resp)"></span>Structure</div>
          <h4>Lungs</h4>
          <p><strong>Right lung:</strong> 3 lobes (superior, middle, inferior). <strong>Left lung:</strong> 2 lobes (cardiac notch accommodates the heart). Each lung is encased in a double-layered pleura — the negative intrapleural pressure keeps the lungs inflated. Air exchange occurs at ~500 million alveoli.</p>
