          <h4>Intercostal Muscles</h4>
          <p><strong>External intercostals:</strong> Elevate the ribs, increasing the anteroposterior and transverse dimensions of the thorax — assist inspiration. <strong>Internal intercostals:</strong> Depress the ribs — primary muscles of forced expiration. Together with the diaphragm, they form the core respiratory pump.</p>
        </div>
