          <button class="pop-close" onclick="closePopup('hs-resp-4')">✕</button>
          <div class="pop-label"><span class="pop-accent" style="background:var(--resp)"></span>Speech Expiration</div>
          <h4>Abdominal Muscles</h4>
          <p>The four abdominal muscles (transversus abdominis, rectus abdominis, internal oblique, external oblique) are the primary drivers of <strong>active expiration for speech</strong>. The transversus abdominis is especially active for maintaining steady subglottal pressure across long utterances. Their coordinated contraction compresses the abdominal contents, pushing the diaphragm upward and expelling air.</p>
        </div>
